					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There's a lot to be said about colours, both in linguistics, and discourse theory. (Discourse here meaning &quot;institutionalized patterns of knowledge (...)&quot;, quote from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discourse_analysis" class="postlink">wik</a>i). <br /><br />It's not just english, either. There seems to be a general pattern in how linguistic distinctions between colours evolved, with local variants. <br /><br />Perception, cognition and memory are all very susceptible to how we categorize things.</div>

					
