				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Sapir-Whorf in a nutshell:<br />If a language lacks a word for blue, its speakers will pay less attention to whether something is blue because it isn't something they'll need to repeat to someone else.<br /><br /><img src="https://static.miraheze.org/allthetropeswiki/thumb/7/7e/Sapir-Worf_hypothesis.jpg/320px-Sapir-Worf_hypothesis.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />Sapir-<em>Worf</em>, on the other hand:<br /><a href="http://klingonska.org/ref/color.html" class="postlink">Klingon basic color names</a> are <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/Orange-Blue_Contrast" class="postlink">orange and blue</a>, with idiomatic use of &quot;more&quot; and &quot;bright&quot; to mean &quot;one or two steps higher in the rainbow&quot;.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

